<paragraph id="F673765427FA3B76F2883050712A180E" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2E43BD207E5894BAC225EEA52A36936" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">
<emphasis id="2FC8B8510248313C966D5AF60FCD125E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Saprobic</emphasis>
on dead culms of 
<taxonomicName id="08097DF4F885005EF5DE5430E7ABC58B" authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Kurz ex Munro" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizostachyum brachycladum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="brachycladum">
<emphasis id="9F1813324D5E3E041ECDCAF476169FEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Schizostachyum brachycladum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A356B3FAEF699324A91EBA967AED16F7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="order">Poales</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8523E0C4D4F20347237586264C993985" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B41F1F2B2E3D2AEFDB4446EB38F46DB1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bambusoideae">Bambusoideae</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="867EF738E6115E1A492C913B4D73867E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: Undetermined. 
<emphasis id="F38857EA875770BC43C664A035391444" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="1221B54A735809E39695888B69B0FB3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Colonies</emphasis>
on natural substrate, superficial, gregarious, scattered, irregular, dark brown to black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0CDA93221177DADF3AC0F0B85C5AE5D7" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F6099956" captionText="Figure 1. Arthrinium bambusicola (MFLU 20 - 0528, holotype). a, b. Appearance of the fungus on dead culms of Schizostachyum brachycladum; c. Conidia with mycelia; d. Mycelia; e-f. Mycelia bearing conidiogenous cells and conidia; h-l. Conidia; m. Germinated conidium; n. forward culture; o. reversed culture. Scale bars: b = 500 μm, c-e = 20 μm, f, g = 10 μm, h-m = 5 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e58755.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469090" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">1</figureCitation>
a-b). 
<emphasis id="53364420CCF97F7B07818EBEFF9CDDBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Mycelium</emphasis>
consisting of branched, septate, hyaline to dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A13487EC088CF394CE00CA81B94E6269" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F6099956" captionText="Figure 1. Arthrinium bambusicola (MFLU 20 - 0528, holotype). a, b. Appearance of the fungus on dead culms of Schizostachyum brachycladum; c. Conidia with mycelia; d. Mycelia; e-f. Mycelia bearing conidiogenous cells and conidia; h-l. Conidia; m. Germinated conidium; n. forward culture; o. reversed culture. Scale bars: b = 500 μm, c-e = 20 μm, f, g = 10 μm, h-m = 5 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e58755.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469090" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">1</figureCitation>
c-e). 
<emphasis id="7316DBD5418C9F29C4E6A3A591E01DF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Conidiophores</emphasis>
0.8-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="D883F6F84EACF9F60BC5B5B17A7A42AB" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam. semi-micronematous to macronematous, mononematous, solitary, branched, flexuous, smooth, hyaline, aseptate when immature, becoming brown, septate when mature (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E148629AE02FCC68EA78FCE48D4B88E8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F6099956" captionText="Figure 1. Arthrinium bambusicola (MFLU 20 - 0528, holotype). a, b. Appearance of the fungus on dead culms of Schizostachyum brachycladum; c. Conidia with mycelia; d. Mycelia; e-f. Mycelia bearing conidiogenous cells and conidia; h-l. Conidia; m. Germinated conidium; n. forward culture; o. reversed culture. Scale bars: b = 500 μm, c-e = 20 μm, f, g = 10 μm, h-m = 5 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e58755.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469090" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">1</figureCitation>
d). 
<emphasis id="C86CAAD3F4009069308EE9B9C15817CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
1.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="0569429D37EC2B572DF6746D814CA7F3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-4 
<normalizedToken id="5262C2596CCFCACB3475463B9866ED4C" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, monoblastic or polyblastic, terminal, determinate, cylindrical, hyaline to light brown, smooth, aggregated, ampulliform, in clusters on aerial mycelium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D1EF2711E641CC9BB9BDD5CFEAF9BDA6" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F6099956" captionText="Figure 1. Arthrinium bambusicola (MFLU 20 - 0528, holotype). a, b. Appearance of the fungus on dead culms of Schizostachyum brachycladum; c. Conidia with mycelia; d. Mycelia; e-f. Mycelia bearing conidiogenous cells and conidia; h-l. Conidia; m. Germinated conidium; n. forward culture; o. reversed culture. Scale bars: b = 500 μm, c-e = 20 μm, f, g = 10 μm, h-m = 5 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e58755.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469090" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">1</figureCitation>
e-g). 
<emphasis id="699BDDB4FE1AF4142B770504FABBA880" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Conidia</emphasis>
pleurogenous, solitary, oval to broadly round or irregularly round, brown to medium brown, guttulate to roughened, granular, in surface view 6-8 
<normalizedToken id="BCFBA9C803E45F775A6DE5D4B333D218" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7.8 
<normalizedToken id="9932B732AE640EE662A22D87CEA8CC5E" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="ED1CB2066CC0AD3E1D0A3A194E8C1E1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">x̅</emphasis>
= 6.5 
<normalizedToken id="2636111F306B268658A35476F17F3B71" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7 
<normalizedToken id="8FAAD7D2117AA71632FE60A637B6BFA2" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 39), in lateral view 3.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="6B726E60D09EF6921595222C48B02D52" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-6.5 
<normalizedToken id="F4568A4331EEFAB9E79F8B1345D7430F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="6A6CAB2279DF3DA7F7B6493D15624803" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">x̅</emphasis>
= 4.5 
<normalizedToken id="3A1D4B988D2663502CE85EAF75ACE388" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 
<normalizedToken id="3FE2FB6D5FA2D8B096650275AD961575" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 39), with finely pale slit at outer edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1288C8B45305EADB3048FB1AA7798F8F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F6099956" captionText="Figure 1. Arthrinium bambusicola (MFLU 20 - 0528, holotype). a, b. Appearance of the fungus on dead culms of Schizostachyum brachycladum; c. Conidia with mycelia; d. Mycelia; e-f. Mycelia bearing conidiogenous cells and conidia; h-l. Conidia; m. Germinated conidium; n. forward culture; o. reversed culture. Scale bars: b = 500 μm, c-e = 20 μm, f, g = 10 μm, h-m = 5 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e58755.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469090" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">1</figureCitation>
h-l).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1DFE489EF2DB20969EE7EC1C7433E3FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" type="culture characteristics">
<paragraph id="4122BC018F5939B7DE1902FB84D7E566" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Culture characteristics</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5FCED4500543EB80614B0E379B37902" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">colonies flat, spreading, with moderate, pale, aerial mycelium. On PDA, surface white, lightly yellow with patches of dirty white, reverse lightly pigmented.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D248641999FFC9A3CDE96CAF5561BC7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" type="facesoffungi number">
<paragraph id="D8134784095B84C01829C2126037A709" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Facesoffungi number</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FC47981DA9266693500DCADEC1BE83E" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">FoF 09162</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02B20AC373C4E1D6AFECAE5DC741BE62" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3D85909578D0C1C35398AF57BA9B8E71" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA0679FEBF0147372A71BDC886F501DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">
Referring to the host from which the holotype was isolated, a member of the bamboo subfamily (
<taxonomicName id="F0243C8531C973EAA6FED21671FC4F14" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bambusoideae">Bambusoideae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C92D1EBB126F7FC019AC5C2BFB6A14DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0C2AC8B0D22E98B15A2854E6341BFF69" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3225E7BD388B6783BA6F3C30F95B6B9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">
<taxonomicName id="EF5F8E82FB131F18C38F8F5642697988" authorityName="X. Tang, K. D. Hyde &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium bambusicola" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis id="88D754F5C542A3A3A69AC049466CBE04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">Arthrinium bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms were retrieved as a sister taxon of 
<taxonomicName id="9CFAE271DD106A72B47183E59193CA70" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gutiae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gutiae">
<emphasis id="1A59D1819414822DA2D0F26CCCBD109A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. gutiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with relatively good support (83 ML, 77 MP, 0.99 PP). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="D0314FCD36B8C0DEC4F9DC8C3C3DB895" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bambusicola" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis id="18CA05E88FAEBD73EB20ABDA64361E72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="E8194BBAB142200EB9F319758A21CBDB" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gutiae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gutiae">
<emphasis id="37945EF8D73A77F1D0519ECF0421CEE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. gutiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having larger conidia [surface view: 5.5-8 
<normalizedToken id="89C290D8C5FF18408A2BB19CC2E874CF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 
<normalizedToken id="EB2AC8A7EC15C5F1F75C741719E211F4" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam., lateral view: 3.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="7F5E6EEBF425DEE026A100A6BFB5F48D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-6.5 
<normalizedToken id="960A74BF505E46A3DC2F21185AC6994E" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam. versus surface view: 4.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="05F08FF00C20DDF80C8F46F9A2B0CAF0" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="37DAF146EF551BBA440029D87A5074DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">x̅</emphasis>
= 5.5 
<normalizedToken id="C7F96D780C91EED1998FBE45FFD12800" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) diam., lateral view: 2-6 
<normalizedToken id="F554F2F2E27B7EF5091052D768558053" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="253F756F90A8D38DFC0CBB0603588BE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">x̅</emphasis>
= 4) diam.] and irregularly rounded, guttulate to roughened conidia (
<taxonomicName id="B9DE99005F796D78A174A5E522BAA762" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gutiae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gutiae">
<emphasis id="0FDAD84D718FCA586E6470750C90CF0A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. gutiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: smooth-walled, globose conidia). The conidiogenous cells of 
<taxonomicName id="FB88E645658E14284F490C8689E005E8" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bambusicola" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis id="18637948DD71CA3F36267CF21C281257" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller (1.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="435DA674618147B4EBAE4CB48F15F640" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-4 
<normalizedToken id="E0631772D319A65FB5655E66FEB67900" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
versus 3-7
<normalizedToken id="24AF0E9C45EAD68F1EB28007C9DABEBF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 
<normalizedToken id="E34B5DE12C6F2C5CC0D5B8B10F5B5E44" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). Based on pairwise nucleotide comparisons, 
<taxonomicName id="0B9B2FB526DAC0F0484702B8418CB96F" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bambusicola" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis id="AACECD65881585E035787B5AA1B147D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName id="2AB04972AA0BF0F7069E945D8CB0AA91" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gutiae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gutiae">
<emphasis id="02407CA8487853972C74D4EB5A264FEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. gutiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 31/ 620 bp (5%) of the ITS, 7/814 (0.98%) of the LSU and 44/342 bp (12%) of TEF1. Based on the combination of morphological characters and sequence data, we consider 
<taxonomicName id="23C8A646456A65A14F5BCF05780B9959" class="Liliopsida" family="Restionaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bambusicola" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis id="4768E8DB51C61419E7EFB404E25A00A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58755">A. bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
